Package: spuR
Title: Spatial Unit Root Tests and Transformations
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Paul", "Boll", email = "david.boll@warwick.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sascha O.", "Becker", role = "aut"),
    person("Hans-Joachim", "Voth", role = "aut"),
    person("Ulrich K.", "Mueller", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original MATLAB implementation"),
    person("Mark W.", "Watson", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original MATLAB implementation")
    )
Description: Implements low-frequency spatial unit root tests and
    spatial transformations for cross-sectional data as developed by
    Mueller and Watson (2024) <doi:10.3982/ECTA20682>. Provides I(0) and
    I(1) tests for detecting spatial unit roots, residual-based variants
    for regression settings, half-life confidence intervals for spatial
    persistence, and spatial transformations (LBM-GLS, nearest-neighbor,
    isotropic, cluster) for correcting spatial dependence. See Becker,
    Boll, and Voth (2025) for a practical guide to these methods.
